50|$|Candy {{making is}} the {{preparation}} of candies and sugar confections. Candy making includes {{the preparation of}} many various <b>candies,</b> such as <b>hard</b> <b>candies,</b> jelly beans, gumdrops, taffy, liquorice, cotton candy, chocolates and chocolate truffles, dragées, fudge, caramel candy and toffee.|$|R
50|$|Walter W. Reid Jr. {{founded the}} Charms Candy Company in 1912. The company was {{originally}} called Tropical Charms, {{a reference to}} the individually wrapped square shaped <b>hard</b> <b>candies,</b> which were {{one of the first to}} be individually wrapped in cellophane.|$|R
